<div class="page-product-care pt-nav">

  <div class="page-hero" style="position:relative;height:40vh;min-height:300px;overflow:hidden;background:#1a1a1a;">
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;padding:2rem;">
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.5rem);color:#fff;margin-bottom:1rem;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Product Care</h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.05rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);max-width:500px;">Preserve the beauty of your DIAZ pieces for a lifetime</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section style="padding:5rem 0;background:#fff;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">

      <div style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;font-size:1.05rem;">
          Fine leather is a natural material that develops a rich patina over time. With proper care, your DIAZ pieces will become more beautiful with each passing year. Follow these guidelines to keep your items looking their best.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom:3.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.6rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5;padding-bottom:0.75rem;">General Leather Care</h2>
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2rem;">
          <div style="background:#f5f0ea;padding:1.75rem;border-radius:4px;">
            <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:#1a1a1a;">Do</h3>
            <ul style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;padding-left:1.1rem;">
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Clean with a soft, dry cloth regularly</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Apply a quality leather conditioner every 3–6 months</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Store in the dust bag provided</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Allow leather to breathe — avoid airtight storage</li>
              <li>Stuff bags with tissue paper when not in use to maintain shape</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="background:#f9f9f9;padding:1.75rem;border-radius:4px;">
            <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;color:#1a1a1a;">Don't</h3>
            <ul style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;padding-left:1.1rem;">
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Expose to direct sunlight for prolonged periods</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Get wet — if it does, let it dry naturally away from heat</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Use chemical cleaners or alcohol-based products</li>
              <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Overstuff bags or wallets</li>
              <li>Store in plastic bags or humid environments</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom:3.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.6rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5;padding-bottom:0.75rem;">Wallets & Small Leather Goods</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          Avoid overfilling your wallet as it can distort the leather and affect the structure over time. Remove unnecessary cards and receipts regularly. Wipe down the exterior with a slightly damp cloth for light cleaning, and follow with a dry cloth.
        </p>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;">
          For scratches on smooth leather, gently rub with your fingertip — the natural oils from your skin can often minimize the appearance of light marks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom:3.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.6rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5;padding-bottom:0.75rem;">Bags & Larger Items</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          When not in use, store your bag upright in its dust bag, stuffed with tissue paper to maintain its shape. Keep hardware clean with a soft, dry cloth. Avoid placing bags on rough surfaces that could scratch the leather.
        </p>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;">
          For structured bags, avoid hanging by the straps for long periods as this can cause them to stretch.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom:3.5rem;">
        <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.6rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e5e5;padding-bottom:0.75rem;">Hardware Care</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;">
          Our hardware is finished to resist tarnishing, but regular maintenance will keep it looking its best. Polish hardware gently with a soft dry cloth. Avoid contact with perfume, lotions, and moisture which can affect the finish over time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#f5f0ea;padding:2rem;border-radius:4px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:var(--font-heading);font-size:1.2rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Professional Cleaning</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">
          For deep cleaning or significant stains, we recommend consulting a professional leather cleaning specialist. If you have any specific care questions about your DIAZ product, our team is happy to help.
        </p>
        <a href="/pages/contact" style="display:inline-block;background:#1a1a1a;color:#fff;padding:0.75rem 2rem;font-size:0.85rem;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;text-decoration:none;">Contact Us</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</div>

<style>
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  .page-product-care [style*="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr"] {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
  }
}
</style>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Product Care Page",
  "tag": "div"
}
{% endschema %}
